Preheat your oven to 220°C. Cut the @potato{2}(cut into wedges about the width of your index finger, no need to peel). Place them on a #lined baking tray{} in a single layer, drizzle over some @oil{} and sprinkle on half the @dried thyme{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until the wedges are crisp and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Place your hand flat on top of one of the chicken breasts and slice into it from the side so it opens like a book. You've now butterflied the chicken! Repeat for all breasts, then pop them in a #bowl{} and add the @BBQ sauce{}, a pinch of @salt{} and some @black pepper{}. Sprinkle in the remaining @thyme{}, and grate over the @lime zest{}.

Rub the flavourings into the @chicken breasts{2} with your hands. Then lay it on another #baking tray{}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{15-17%minutes}. Don't leave any marinade behind! Spread it all onto the chicken before it goes in the oven.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken is cooking, cut each @ciabatta{2} in half horizontally. In the last 5 mins of potato cooking time, pop the ciabattas on top of the wedges to warm. Squeeze the @lime juice{1/2%lemon} into a bowl and add the @honey{} and @olive oil{}. Mix together. This is the salad dressing!

> TIP: Only dress the salad right at the last minute or the leaves will wilt.

Once the ciabattas are warm, spread some of the @mayonnaise{} onto the bottom half of each. Assemble the sandwiches by laying the chicken on top of this (drizzle over any cooking juices if you like) and adding a few @salad leaves{} (only use a third). Pop on the top half of the ciabatta. Add the remaining salad leaves to the bowl of dressing and toss.

Serve your BBQ chicken ciabattas with potato wedges and some dressed salad on the side. Enjoy!